
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Compiling the model: 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	
	You may need to edit the makefile to set the path to your compiled NetCDF and FFTW libraries
	Also to set the compiler for your machine if necessary
		defaults to gfortran I think...
	
	make clean
	
	make
	
	options: 
		DEBUG=fast			fast compile and moderately strong optimization
		DEBUG=debug			debug compile with optimizations
		DEBUG=debugslow		debug compile w/o optimizations
		DEBUG=debugomp		debug compile with optimizations and OpenMP parallelization
		DEBUG=debugompslow	debug compile w/o optimizations but with OpenMP parallelization
		

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Running the model: 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Required Input files/variables

	icar_options.nml
		This file specifies all other files and options.  
	
	Necessary netcdf files: 
		Boundary/Initial conditions in e.g. wrf output files
			must [optionally] contain QVAPOR, [QCLOUD], [QICE], T, P, [PB], U, V, HGT, Z, LAT, LONG
		Hi resolution DEM in e.g. high-res wrf input or output file
			must contain HGT, LAT, LONG
			
	NOTE namelist file in git repo is not always in sync with code!

